comment: Gortat (WAS) sets the screen on Schroder (ATL) and continues moving into him, affecting his ability to defend the play.
Bazemore (ATL) makes contact to Gortat's (WAS) body that affects his dunk attempt.
Millsap (ATL) sets the screen on Beal (WAS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Beal (WAS) makes incidental contact with Millsap (ATL) that does not affect his SQBR.
Beal (WAS) is in a legal guarding position and deflects the ball away from Millsap (ATL). Following the deflection, Beal makes incidental contact with Millsap's arm.
Hardaway Jr. (ATL) and Gortat (WAS) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Beal (WAS) makes marginal contact with Schroder (ATL) that does not affect his SQBR.
Schroder (ATL) fumbles the ball but does not gather it with two hands before continuing his dribble.
Gortat (WAS) sets the screen on Schroder (ATL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.

Gortat (WAS) establishes a wide screening position and absorbs the contact from Hardaway, Jr. (ATL). He then moves in the same direction and path as Hardaway, Jr. and briefly engages with him, but the contact is marginal.
Gortat (WAS) makes contact to the body of Millsap (ATL) that affects his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Gortat (WAS) sets the screen on Schroder (ATL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Millsap (ATL) makes marginal contact with Wall (WAS) that does not affect his shot attempt.
Prince (ATL) makes incidental contact with Gortat's (WAS) body that does not affect his shot attempt.
Bazemore (ATL) pushes Gortat (WAS) and the contact affects his shot attempt.
